<p>A lot of inspiration for this living collection comes from <a href="https://css-irl.info">Michelle Barker</a>, who wrote about upcoming browser features <a href="https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2022/03/new-css-features-2022/">on Smashing Magazine</a> and on <a href="https://css-irl.info/exciting-times-for-browsers-and-css/">CSS { In Real Life }</a>.</p>

<p>Please feel free to <a href="https://github.com/{{ author.github }}/{{ site.repository }}/tree/main/src/data/browserFeatures.json">suggest new features</a> or even <a href="https://github.com/{{ author.github }}/{{ site.repository }}/tree/main/src/data/browsersByType.json">other browsers</a>.</p>

<figure>
	<table>
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<td></td>
				{% for browser in browsersByType %}
					<th class=" [ sideways ] ">{{ browser.name }}</th>
				{% endfor %}
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			{% for feature in browserFeaturesSorted %}
				{% caniuse_table_row feature %}
			{% endfor %}
		</tbody>
	</table>
</figure>

<hr>

{% for feature in browserFeaturesSorted %}
	<section class=" [ flow ] ">
		<h2 id="{{ feature.id }}">{{ feature.title | safe }}{% if feature.language %} <small>¬∑ {{ feature.language | capitalizeFormat }}</small>{% endif %}</h2>
		{{ feature.description | markdownFormat | safe }}
		<ul>
			{% for link in feature.links %}
				<li>{{ link | markdownFormat | safe }}</li>
			{% endfor %}
		</ul>
		{% caniuse feature.id %}
	</section>
{% endfor %}

